<br>
Overview</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
The Savage has turned out to be one of the premiere melee classes of the game.  We have solid offense and defense, with the added strategic element of our many self-buffs.  It is fun to play this class because of the variety of different choices each individual combat encounter presents.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Concerns</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
As new Savages level up, they are presented with difficulties that exceed those of other melee classes.  At these lower levels, for HTH Savages in particular, high miss rates plague solo PvE combat; this makes even soloing on yellows risky business.  In addition, the Savage requires use of their self-buffs in order to win many of these encounters.  The cost of the buffs means longer downtime after the fight is over than other melee classes. <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Specline Issues</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
- HTH Line: S/D/T/Q rate is not working as advertised.  The rate explained to me at class inception was 50% single, 30% double, 15% triple, 5% quadruple.  I have documented rates more around 60/25/2/13 many times.<br>
- HTH Line: Totemic Fear is an evade reactionary style, yet has a snare proc attached to it.  Suggest altering this proc to a high-end bleed.<br>
- HTH Line: Kelgor's Might has a PBAE haste-debuff proc attached which breaks mez on any target within range, yet does not interrupt casting.  Suggest altering the haste-debuff to no longer break mez in PvE.<br>
- HTH Line: Clan's Might does not offer improvement over repeated Clan's Call use. There is a small damage improvement over Clan's Call, but there is no to-hit bonus and the benefits of the multi-target aspect are unrealized in the system's current implementation.<br>
- HTH Line: Totemic Sacrifice, the 50-spec style is not as useful as it could be.  The damage output is not much greater than previous styles in the chain, and while the lack of endurance cost is a small perk, the benefits of the multi-target aspect are unrealized in the system's current implementation.<br>
- Sword/Hammer/Axe Lines: All longer duration stuns in these three lines are based on a shield-block reactionary style.  There are no evade reactionary styles in these lines and the parry reactionary stuns are very short, yet more classes in Midgard who can spec these weapons are capable of evading an speccing parry than can spec in shield.  Suggest altering the lines to incorporate a long duration stun chain based on evade or parry somewhere.<br>
- Savagery Line: When the interruption feature of the insta-taunt is removed, it is requested that the recast timer be shortened (since the interrupt was the primary reason the recast timer was in place).<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>New Issues</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
- I am not aware of new issues as a result of changes made in 1.63 or 1.64.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Other Issues</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
- There are no left-hand wieldable hammers or swords.  <br>
- No slower weapons (&gt;3.4s) have been found in Tuscarien Glacier.  <br>
- Additional style animations needed to visually tell the difference between some styles.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Item Problems</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
- As a result of both fast attacks and hitting up to 4 times in a single combat round, HTH weaponry degrades at a much faster rate than other weaponry - this poses an issue for harder-to-get items and ultimately increases costs of maintaining weaponry.<br>
- There is no HTH weapon reward for the &quot;Ancestral Secrets&quot; quest.   <br>
